        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 2:24PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 224 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southwest of Barnhart, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Barnhart and The Intersection Of Us 190 And Highway 163.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 359 and 360.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
